      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how training data poisoning occurs in real-world settings and why it poses a serious risk to machine learning systems. You will examine practical examples of corrupted datasets and see how even small, deliberate changes to training data can lead to unreliable or harmful outcomes. The lesson breaks down the key methods used to introduce poisoned data, helping you recognise the warning signs before they cause significant damage. By working through concrete scenarios, you will build a clearer understanding of how these attacks unfold and what makes certain systems more vulnerable than others. No prior technical expertise is required, as the focus is on building practical awareness rather than deep mathematical knowledge.",
